sequenceDiagram
  title Store Associate Looks Up Customer Cart via Loyalty QR at POS
  accTitle: POS cart lookup with per-item availability and cache-miss failure path
  accDescr: Store associate scans loyalty QR code at POS. Apollo Gateway validates the associate session and resolves the customer identity via Identity Service, fetches the active cart from Cart Service, then enriches each line item with shelf availability from the Inventory Read Cache. One item (SKU TRL-X9-42) returns a cache miss — the Cart Service marks it unavailable and the POS renders a "not at this store" row with an alternative-store suggestion.

  participant POS as POS Client
  participant Gateway as Apollo Gateway
  participant Identity as Identity Service
  participant Cart as Cart Service
  participant Inventory as Inventory Read Cache
  participant SAP as SAP ECC

  Note over POS,SAP: p95 latencies shown per step — measured within same AWS region (eu-west-1)

  Store Associate->>POS: scans customer loyalty QR code
  Note right of POS: QR payload: loyalty account ID + store ID

  POS->>Gateway: lookupCustomerCart(qrCode, storeId)
  Note right of POS: GraphQL mutation
  Note left of Gateway: p95 ≤ 80ms (store WiFi + TLS)

  critical Validate associate session
    Gateway->>Identity: validateAssociateSession(associateToken)
    Note right of Gateway: gRPC unary · p95 ≤ 15ms
    Identity-->>Gateway: { valid: true, storeId: "high-st-01", permissions: ["pos:cart:read"] }
    Note left of Identity: p95 ≤ 15ms
  end

  critical Resolve customer from QR
    Gateway->>Identity: resolveLoyaltyQr(qrCode)
    Note right of Gateway: gRPC unary · p95 ≤ 15ms
    Identity-->>Gateway: { customerId: "cust-8421", loyaltyTier: "gold", givenName: "Alex" }
    Note left of Identity: p95 ≤ 15ms
    Note over Identity: tier lookup from local PostgreSQL · no external call
  end

  critical Fetch active cart
    Gateway->>Cart: getActiveCart(customerId)
    Note right of Gateway: gRPC unary · p95 ≤ 15ms
    Cart-->>Gateway: { cartId: "cart-9f3a", items: [ ... ] }
    Note left of Cart: p95 ≤ 15ms (cart held in session Redis)
  end

  Note over Gateway: cart contains 3 line items — enrich each with per-store availability

  loop For each cart item (SKU, requestedQty)
    Cart->>Inventory: getStock(storeId, sku)
    Note right of Cart: RESP GET · p95 ≤ 3ms per lookup
    alt Cache hit — shelf stock found (items 1 and 3)
      Inventory-->>Cart: { sku: "LMP-100", qtyOnShelf: 4, sellThroughToday: 8, lastSync: "10:29 UTC" }
      Note left of Inventory: p95 ≤ 3ms
      Note over Cart: status ← "available" · no SAP call needed
    else Cache miss — no batch data for this SKU at this store (item 2: TRL-X9-42)
      Inventory-->>Cart: null
      Note left of Inventory: p95 ≤ 3ms · key absent — falling back to SAP ECC inline
      Cart->>SAP: checkStockRealtime(storeId, sku)
      Note right of Cart: IDoc synchronous lookup · bypasses 15–30 min batch cycle
      Note left of SAP: p95 ≤ 400ms · WAN + ERP query overhead
      alt SAP confirms stock on hand
        SAP-->>Cart: { sku: "TRL-X9-42", qtyOnHand: 2, warehouseBin: "B-12", lastPhysicalCount: "09:15 UTC" }
        Note left of SAP: p95 ≤ 400ms
        Note over Cart: status ← "available (SAP-confirmed)"<br/>+400ms penalty vs cache hit
      else SAP cannot confirm — source-of-truth has no record
        SAP-->>Cart: { sku: "TRL-X9-42", status: "not-found", reason: "no-stock-at-location" }
        Note left of SAP: p95 ≤ 400ms
        Note over Cart: status ← "unavailable"<br/>confirmed by SAP source-of-truth<br/>+400ms penalty vs cache hit
      end
    end
  end

  Note over Cart: enriched cart assembled — p95 total for this step:<br/>cache-hit items (LMP-100, LMP-200): +3ms each<br/>cache-miss item (TRL-X9-42): +3ms cache check + 400ms SAP fallback = +403ms

  Cart-->>Gateway: enriched cart with per-item availability status
  Note left of Cart: gRPC unary · p95 ≤ 15ms

  Gateway-->>POS: { cart, customer: { name, loyaltyTier }, items: [{ sku, name, qty, availability: { status, qtyOnShelf, freshness, source } }] }
  Note left of Gateway: JSON/HTTPS · p95 ≤ 80ms

  Note over POS: POS renders cart view: "Alex (Gold)"<br/>✓ LMP-100 — 4 on shelf (checked 12 min ago) · cache<br/>⚠ TRL-X9-42 — 2 on hand (SAP-confirmed) · +400ms<br/>✓ LMP-200 — 2 on shelf (checked 8 min ago) · cache

  Note over POS,SAP: ⏱ LATENCY TOTALS<br/>Happy path (all cache hits): 80+15+15+15+15+(3×3)+15+80 = <b>~250ms p95</b><br/>Failure path (1 cache miss → SAP fallback): 80+15+15+15+15+(2×3)+3+400+15+80 = <b>~650ms p95</b><br/>Worst case (3 cache misses → 3 SAP calls in sequence): 80+15+15+15+15+3×(3+400)+15+80 = <b>~1,450ms p95</b>

  Store Associate->>POS: taps unavailable item for alternatives
  POS->>Gateway: suggestAlternativeStores(sku: "TRL-X9-42", excludeStoreId)
  Note right of POS: GraphQL query · p95 ≤ 80ms
  Gateway->>Inventory: getStockForAllStores(sku)
  Note right of Gateway: RESP MGET across store keys · p95 ≤ 10ms
  Inventory-->>Gateway: [{ storeId: "riverside-01", qtyOnShelf: 3, distance: 2.4km }, { storeId: "oakfield-01", qtyOnShelf: null, lastSync: ">30min" }]
  Gateway-->>POS: { alternatives: [{ storeName: "Riverside Mall", qtyOnShelf: 3, distance: "2.4 km" }] }
  Note left of Gateway: JSON/HTTPS · p95 ≤ 80ms

  Note over POS: Associate tells customer:<br/>"TRL-X9-42 isn't at this store, but Riverside Mall has 3 —<br/>want me to transfer your cart?"

  Note over POS,SAP: LATENCY vs PSD2 SCA BUDGET (1500ms target)<br/>Happy path all cache hits: 250ms p95. 6x below budget.<br/>1 cache miss SAP fallback: 650ms p95. 2.3x below budget.<br/>3 cache misses 3x SAP: 1450ms p95. At budget ceiling.<br/>Worst stage: SAP inline IDoc at 400ms p95 per call.<br/>Bottleneck: SAP ECC inline lookup dominates when cache misses. Mitigation 1: cache warm-up on Kafka stock events. Mitigation 2: degrade to stock unknown on cache miss.
